<ul>
    <li>Use camelCase for variable names</li>
    <li>Use PascalCase for function names</li>
    <li>Use strict mode ("use strict") when possible</li>
    <li>Use === when possible</li>
    <li>Initialize variables when declared</li>
    <li>Provide a single place to initialize variables</li>
    <li>Use parameter/argument defaults</li>
</ul>

<p>Use and set parameter/argument defaults like so:</p>

<pre>
<code>
function myFunction(x, y)
{
    if (y === undefined)
    { y = 0; }
}
</code>
</pre>

